Key Formulas
Usable Hosts = 2^(host bits) - 2
Number of Subnets = 2^(subnet bits)
CIDR Notation: /prefix length
Wildcard Mask = 255.255.255.255 - Subnet Mask
Start: Given Network
e.g., 192.168.1.0/24

Calculate Host Bits:
2^n - 2 ≥ hosts
(n = host bits)
Calculate Subnet Bits:
2^s ≥ subnets
(s = subnet bits)
Total bits = 32?
Network + Subnet

Invalid: Adjust

Determine New Prefix:
Original prefix + subnet bits
e.g., /24 + 4 bits = /28
Calculate Subnet Mask:
/28 = 255.255.255.240
(11111111.11111111.11111111.11110000)
Calculate Magic Number:
256 - last octet = increment
256 - 240 = 16
